{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a three month \"qualifying period\" for Prime Minister PDCA eligibility",
        "additional_details": "It would seem grossly inappropriate for any Prime Minister to be eligible for PDCA if serving less than a minimum of 3 months in the role.",
        "background": "Former Prime Ministers are eligible to claim Public Duties Cost Allowance (PDCA), currently set at a limit of \u00a3115,000 per annum. This petition proposes a qualifying period of 3 months tenure of office as Prime Minister of the UK before former post holders can be considered eligible to claim PDCA.",
